You are a principal software architect, senior Go engineer, DevOps engineer, and Flutter architect.

You must build a production-ready, scalable fitness SaaS platform named FITFLOW.

This is not a demo project.
This must be enterprise-grade and scalable to 1M+ users.

========================================
GLOBAL RULES
========================================

- Use Clean Architecture
- Follow SOLID principles
- Use dependency injection
- No global state
- Context passed everywhere
- Structured logging (zap or zerolog)
- Proper error wrapping
- Graceful shutdown
- Horizontal scalability
- Write production-ready code only
- No pseudo-code
- No simplified examples
- Split code into proper files
- Add comments explaining design decisions
- Add basic unit tests
- Add integration test example
- Generate OpenAPI spec
- Provide folder tree before code

If something is complex — split it into multiple files.

========================================
STACK
========================================

Backend:
- Go 1.22+
- Gin or Fiber
- PostgreSQL 15+
- Redis 7+
- sqlc (preferred) or GORM
- JWT (access + refresh)
- UUID primary keys
- Clean architecture modular monolith
- Event-driven components using internal event bus
- Background workers
- Rate limiting
- Structured logging
- Prometheus metrics
- Health check endpoint
- OpenTelemetry tracing ready

Frontend:
- Flutter (single codebase)
- Riverpod or Bloc
- REST client
- Environment configs
- Proper architecture (data/domain/presentation layers)
- Error handling
- Loading states

Infra:
- Docker (multi-stage builds)
- Docker Compose (local)
- Kubernetes manifests
- HPA
- Ingress
- ConfigMaps
- Secrets
- Separate Redis + Postgres
- Readiness and liveness probes
- CI pipeline example (GitHub Actions)

Storage:
- S3-compatible (MinIO)
- filesystem (local)

========================================
ARCHITECTURE
========================================

Backend structure:

/cmd/api
/internal
    /domain
    /usecase
    /repository
    /delivery/http
    /delivery/middleware
    /events
    /workers
    /config
    /pkg
/migrations
/deployments/docker
/deployments/k8s
/docs

Use modular monolith with clear domain boundaries:

Modules:
- Auth
- User
- Gym
- Workout
- Progress
- Health
- Social
- Blog
- Trainer
- Notification

